A vintage-style illustration of a brass mechanical scale from the 1920s era, with one pan holding a small, intricately detailed ice cream cone and the other pan holding a collection of tiny brass gears and cogs. The scale sits on a weathered wooden workbench scattered with architectural blueprints and measurement tools like calipers and rulers. Warm sepia tones dominate the scene with dramatic shadows cast by soft amber light from an unseen window. The background shows faded workshop walls with subtle patina. The composition emphasizes balance and precision, with careful attention to metallic textures and aged paper surfaces.
